[30;1m37 | [0m[35mclient tells the server what hostname it is contacting. This is important[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35mwhen servers are using `Virtual Hosting`_. When such servers are hosting[0m
[30;1m39 | [0m[35mmore than one SSL site they need to be able to return the appropriate[0m
[30;1m40 | [0m[35mcertificate based on the hostname the client is connecting to.[0m

[30;1m43 | [0m[35m[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m316[0m[34m of [0m[33m1189[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000704[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Hostname[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/niquests-3.14.0/docs/community/faq.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m.hostname[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35mcorrect (for example, because you can visit the site with your browser).[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m36 | [0m[35m`Server-Name-Indication`_, or SNI, is an official extension to SSL where the[0m
[30;1m37 | [0m[35mclient tells the server what hostname it is contacting. This is important[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35mwhen servers are using `Virtual Hosting`_. When such servers are hosting[0m
[30;1m39 | [0m[35mmore than one SSL site they need to be able to return the appropriate[0m
[30;1m40 | [0m[35mcertificate based on the hostname the client is connecting to.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m317[0m[34m of [0m[33m1189[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000704[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.DataExfiltration.Hostname[0m
  Severity: [36mImportant[0m, Confidence: [36mLow[0m
  Filename: [33m/niquests-3.14.0/docs/community/faq.rst[0m
   Pattern: [32m.hostname[0m
[30;1m29 | [0m[35m-----------------------------------------[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35mThese errors occur when :ref:`SSL certificate verification <verification>`[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35mfails to match the certificate the server responds with to the hostname[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35mNiquests thinks it's contacting. If you're certain the server's SSL setup is[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35mcorrect (for example, because you can visit the site with your browser).[0m
[30;1m35 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m108 | [0m[35mRequest and Response Objects[0m
[30;1m109 | [0m[35m----------------------------[0m
[30;1m110 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m114 | [0m[35mobject is generated once Niquests gets a response back from the server.[0m

[30;1m1312 | [0m[35mraises an error or explicit warning.[0m
